Pre-Game Insights: Coach Desiree Ellis likened the 2024 Olympic qualifier against Nigeria to a boxing match where a knockout is needed to win.
The first leg will be played in Abuja on April 5, while the second leg will take place at Loftus Stadium on April 9.
Banyana Banyana won the 2022 Women's Africa Cup of Nations and reached the last 16 of the World Cup in 2023.
Midfielder Refiloe Jane and defenders Bambanani Mbane, Sibulele Holweni, and Bongeka Gamede are returning from injuries.
The game has been moved to 5pm due to heat concerns.
